reviewText: Ahh yes we return here with the second half of Season 2, the last with the original Hey Arnold(someone else replaced him in season 3).  They don't make shows for kids anymore like they used too, my sister is 9 and will watch these shows with me sometimes because she likes them better, the only shows we watch together that are her shows that she is growing up with is Regular Show and Adventure time because it brings back a lot of the older cartoon styles(plus regular show is like stuck in the 90s they have a master system). But Season 2 still had some classic episodes, Steely Phil & Quantity Time, Eating Contest & Rhonda's Glasses, Helga's Boyfriend & Crush on Teacher, Eugene Goes Bad & Whats Opera, Arnold? I remember watching these on Saturday morning as a kid. There still as good then as they are now, and im glad shout is finally releasing them the way they should be!

reviewText: Part 2 of Season 2 features more classic memories from this beloved 90's TV show. Arnold enters an eating contest, Rhonda the coolest girl in school gets glasses, Eugene rebels, Phoebe once very timid becomes a feared hall-monitor, and the class does their very own opera together.Once again the DVD is distributed with good quality, not outstanding, but a good letterbox picture, it's greatly enhanced from the last version of this DVD but it's nothing you'd praise for being High Definition or vivid. I won't deduct any stars for the lack of extra content because the show you're getting is so original but I should note again that these DVD's are bare bones episodes but one should care more when the original content is so great, a behind the scenes look at are beloved show from the producers would be greatly appreciated. This time the episodes are listed in the order they aired on Nickelodeon.
